entries.femaleVariant: Ah, V. Lemme guess, you called to tell me you're done bashing your head against the wall?
Well... not exactly. We found something.
Uh-huh, 'fraid so. Like you said – he's a ghost. No trace to be found.
entries.maleVariant: Mh, afraid so. Like you said – he's a ghost. No trace to be found.

entries.femaleVariant: No...? Uh, no, I-I meant the... the royal "We." So, about Swedenborg... It's all a big hoax.
entries.maleVariant: No, uh, I meant the royal "We." So, about Swedenborg... It's all a big hoax.

entries.femaleVariant: It's an automated fortune-teller. Strings words into deep-sounding mumbo-jumbo. Someone jacked it into the Net... Probably laughin' from his chair...
Shit, V... This, this...! Oh, this story's even better than I thought! I'll take it from here. Oh, your, uh... your eddies – on their way now. Thanks, bye!
See? Told ya. You've got the making's a media vulture yet, though.
Anyway... Thanks for lookin' into it. Catch you around.
I thought about givin' you a piece of my mind, but... Maybe it's for the best. Every joke needs an audience, right?
Good move, V. Who knows... Hundred, two hundred years from now, when we're all radioactive dust, Swedenborg'll still be preaching on the Net...
